CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 27, 1962, pg. 13, reads: "At YMCA Membership Meeting - This band from Herron Hill Junior High School provided music at the most recent meeting in Centre Avenue "Y" membership drive. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Eight young men from Herron Hill Junior High School marching band, playing brass instruments, with man in center conducting, standing in semi circle in Centre Avenue YMCA gymnasium with model of horse wearing suit in foreground, tote boards inscribed "Red Circle Ranch" and "Buff Ranch" and signs for YMCA along back wall, for "Y" membership drive
